column1: 2023-08-26T12:08:15Z,,3700019,AI,,newgraph_airvine,3700019,newgraph_airvine,1996976,240,Tributary to Kerry Lake,Highway 97,,MOTI          ,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,1.8,36,"100% backwatered culvert with lots of beaver activity and wetland area upstream. Inlet drop is created by beaver generated shrub material so backwatering is happening. However, there is a step of approximately 0.6 m at the top end of the pipe. Black algae throughout channel downstream.  Downstream channel appears to be constructed of rock at approximately 3.8 m wide before entering more beaverdam influenced wetland habitat.           chris_culvert_id: 1996976. 12:08:15",,2023-08-26,10,514827.2348026614,6059932.498898566,No,0.3,No,Yes,100,3,0,0.4,Yes,0.5,5,1,Yes,No,Deep Fill,Medium,,,,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,1,1,2,4, Low gradient and low energy system with likely active fever management happening by MOTI. No evidence of erosion but significant amount of material at inlet of the pipe to the beaver activity appears as though the downstream channel has been made with machines likely to facilitate drainage upstream.          ,1,1,1,5,"Climate risk seems low due to the low energy character of the system. Although the road could be over topped, it seems unlikely that the road prison would be damaged in the event of a flood.          ",10,5,9,,10,2,,,On the main highway very expensive to fix. Impacts of construction likely low due to the wetland lake habitat below buffering. Although no fish confirmed upstream it is connected to fish bearing waters downstream so presents seems likely.          ,20230826_122440.jpg,20230826_122456.jpg,20230826_122520.jpg,20230826_122500.jpg,20230826_122451.jpg,20230826_122505.jpg,,,20230826_122553.jpg,20230826_122640.jpg,20230826_122558.jpg,,Manmade chan ds,,"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN"" ""http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd"">

column1: 2023-08-26T13:37:33Z,,3700024,AI,,newgraph_airvine,3700024,newgraph_airvine,1997302,243,42 Mile Creek,Highway 97,,MOTI,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,2,26,"Nice stream with good flow and abundant gravel, suitably sized for spawning. Culvert is 100% backwatered and fully embedded. It appears as though there have been some very high flow events that have moved significant amounts of gravel, substrate, upstream and downstream. See photos. Channel seems overly straight and deep so suspect machine work has been done to dredge out the crossing, upstream and downstream.                    chris_culvert_id: 1997302. 13:37:33",,2023-08-26,10,510950.2699702871,6072478.815349046,Yes,0.25,Yes,Yes,100,1.5,0,0.3,No,0.5,2.5,1.5,No,No,Deep Fill,High,,,,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,1,1,1,3," Other than evidence of potential dredging  work upstream and downstream, the pipe and road fill appears to be in good shape.",2,3,6,9,"As there is not a lot of fill on top of the pipe, and because of the evidence of significant substrate deposition, it appears there is some risk that this pipe could be plugged with substrate, and blow out the road.          ",10,5,7,4,10,5,41,50,"oh, is this pipe has minimal amounts of fill on it costs are expected to be lower than other crossings in the area. Environmental risks of the work seem slightly higher than other spots we see in the area because of high value habitat with what appears to be gravel suitable for spawning throughout the downstream area          ",20230826_135950.jpg,20230826_140012.jpg,20230826_140026.jpg,20230826_140018.jpg,20230826_140008.jpg,20230826_140021.jpg,,,,20230826_140113.jpg,20230826_140039.jpg,20230826_140057.jpg,Gravels,Substrate adulation,"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN"" ""http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd"">

Stream dry at the time of assessment. Partially vegetated channel upstream, and downstream indicates that the system has not flowed heavily perennially for some time. Wetland type habitat upstream with nice gravels and classic stream character downstream.  Baffles installed within the pipe. Approximately 1/3 of the pipe is blocked from beaver debris near inlet.  chris_culvert_id: 1997288. 14:12:18",,2023-08-26,10,509646.196263646,6074530.730176418,No,,No,No,,10,0.5,0,No,1,3.9,3,Yes,No,Deep Fill,Low,,,,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,1,1,2,4, Approximately 1/3 of the pipe walked through the beaver debris near inlet. Costs were considered fairly high, but moderated by horizontal drill. column1: 2023-08-26T15:14:21Z,,2200009,AI,,,2200009,,1997018,245,Tributary to McLeod Lake,Highway 97,,MOTI,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,1.2,30,"Very nice stream with good flows an abundant gravel. Healthy riparian with evidence of beaver activity, including dam, approximately 5 m downstream of outlet which has backwatered the entire structure, including the outlet of the pipe, which is approximately 10 cm below the surface. It appears as though the crossing has been dredged with a machine recently, both upstream and downstream to deal with substrate deposition. There is pavement armouring the inlet area of the road prism.                    chris_culvert_id: 1997018. 15:14:21",,2023-08-26,10,506481.3990083485,6080584.337296059,Yes,0.1,Yes,Yes,100,1.2,0,1,No,2.5,4.1,2.5,Yes,No,Deep Fill,High,,,,,,,,,,,,,,1,3,1,5,"It appears as though this culvert is within a depositional zone, as substrate has been stretched out from the inlet and outlet areas. There is pavement armouring the inlet area of the road prism.",5,5,25,30,"This crossing seems at high risk due to the low amount of fill above the pipe, beaver activity, armour and evidence of ongoing maintenance to keep the area clear.          ",10,5,2,2,10,3,32,62," Expecting that, this would be a complicated and expensive fix to replace with an open bottom structure due to the need to raise the roads significantly. column1: 2023-08-31T09:51:08Z,,3702919,AI MD,,newgraph_airvine,3702919,newgraph_airvine,,266,Tributary to Crooked River,Davie-Muskeg FSR,,Winton Global Lumber Ltd.,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,1.75,30,"Surprisingly large drainage with good flow. Huge outlet drop and pipe is in very bad shape. Extra 3 m of culvert has been added to the downstream side and is sloping the opposite direction to draining. Large amounts of algae in the channel downstream. Massive amounts of erosion in the downstream channel indicating there are very high flows during runoff. Upstream side of pipe is completely blocked by a beaver dam, creating a wetland upstream.          09:51:08",,2023-08-31,10,509951.7419659927,6040984.4087146465,No,,No,No,,4,1.1,0.65,Yes,3,4.3,2.5,No,No,Deep Fill,Medium,,,,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,5,2,2,9," Downstream has extensive erosion for over 50 m were both banks are blown out during high flow periods. Road fill on the downstream side has extensive runneling  and it appears as some rock was placed as armor. Also, there is a approximately 3 m long chunk of pipe that has been tacked on to the outlet. Indicating outlet is being buried by road fill. Upstream side of pipe is completely blocked by a beaver dam creating wetland upstream.          ",2,2,4,13,"large amount of fill above. The pipe may buffer a flood event from flying over the road and eroding out the fill. Consequence would be primarily related to industrial activity in the watershed, as there are no communities beyond .         ",7,1,6,6,10,8,38,51," Assuming fish bearing because of low gradients, and no stream crossing barriers upstream. Large amount of fill would increase the costs.",20230831_101253.jpg,20230831_101313.jpg,20230831_101328.jpg,20230831_101318.jpg,20230831_101307.jpg,20230831_101322.jpg,20230831_101333.jpg,20230831_101647.jpg,20230831_101433.jpg,,,,,,"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN"" ""http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd"">

column1: 2023-08-31T10:35:13Z,,3702923,Al MD,,newgraph_airvine,3702923,newgraph_airvine,,267,Tributary to Crooked River,Davie-Muskeg FSR,22.5,Winton Global Lumber Ltd.,Closed Bottom Structure,Round Culvert,,1.75,43,Pipe is in extremely bad condition. There are collapsed sections at the edge of the road prism both upstream and downstream. The inlet of the pipe is elevated well above the stream surface as the centre of the pipe has been pressed down by the road fill overtime. Lots of flow must be going underneath the pipe.  Large system with decent flow. Some gravels suitable for spawning downstream.           10:35:13,,2023-08-31,10,510784.9747999946,6040577.752661861,No,,No,No,,9,0.4,0.63,No,3,2.7,2,No,No,Deep Fill,Medium,,,,,,,,,,,,,newgraph_airvine,2,2,3,7,Culvert has failed at the edge of the road prism both upstream and downstream. Very bad condition. The inlet of the pipe is elevated well above the stream surface as the centre of the pipe has been pressed down by the road fill overtime. Lots of flow must be going underneath the pipe.          ,5,3,15,22,"As the water must be pinched through the pipe at multiple positions, it seems likely that some sort of road failure will be happening eventually. Large amount of flil upstream will be washed into the channel below.          ",7,2,6,3,10,4,32,54,"Large amounts of roadshow would make construction difficult. No communities up the road from here as its a FSR. Assuming fish bearing, because no known barriers downstream.          ",20230831_105940.jpg,20230831_110010.jpg,20230831_110034.jpg,20230831_110016.jpg,20230831_110007.jpg,20230831_110020.jpg,20230831_110039.jpg,,,20230831_110234.jpg,,,,,"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN"" ""http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd"">
